seats <- c(rep('Seats-Patio', 74), rep('Seats-Inside',74))
seatcount <-c(`Seats-Patio`, `Seats-Inside`)
df<-data.frame(seats, seatcount)
plot(seatcount~seats, data = df)

aovresult<-aov(seatcount~seats, data = df)
summary(aovresult)
##              Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)    
## seats         1  94612   94612   451.7 <2e-16 ***
## Residuals   146  30583     209                   
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

#1. Correlation was carried out on all variables against sales, it is found that Average Monthly Salad Sales(0.603023013) and Average Monthly Rice Krispy Sales(0.630137441) are highly correlated with the Annual Sales Per Sq Ft and all other variables have weak or negalive correlation with the sales.
#2. ANOVA was run to check the effect of seats-inside and seats-outside on different restaurants. The Anova model shows very high f-value(451.7) and very low p-value which provides evidence that seating arraingments have significant effect on different restaurants. 
#3. ANOVA was run to check if there is any difference in salads sales and RiceKrispies sales at different restaurants. From the boxplot we can see that their is a significant difference. The Anova model shows high f-value and very low p-value which implies that there is significant difference in the sales of Salad and riceKrisples in the restaurant.
#4. ANOVA was run to check if there is any difference in the means of sales of different variables like Alcohol, Protien, Breads and desserts etc in the restaurant. The Anova model shows high f-value and very low p-value which implies that there is significant difference in the sales of different items in the restaurant.
#5. T-test was performed to check if mean of Salesgrowth% is equal to 10. Since p-value is less than  0.05, the alternate hypothesis is true where mean of SalesGrowth% is less than 10.
#6. Time series analysis is conducted on salad sales and RiceKrispies sales for months January to December. The results shows that both have highest sales in the month of May.
